1.00	Wax_thermostatic_elements	Wax thermostatic element	The wax thermostatic element was invented by Sergius Vernet in 1936 . The principal application of the wax element technology is for the production of automotive thermostats. The first applications of this technology in the plumbing and heating industries were in Sweden (1970) and in Switzerland (1971).	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/76/Carthermostat.jpg/220px-Carthermostat.jpg
